news.title: Home prices in Hong Kong fall by 1.7% in February
news.para: Home prices in one of the world's most expensive property markets dropped 1.7% in February from the previous month, official data showed on Tuesday, following a revised 1.2% fall in January.

news.title: Land prices in Japan rise by 2.3% in 2023
news.para: Average nationwide land prices rose 2.3% in the year through January 1, the strongest pace of growth since a 11.3% gain in 1991 when land prices started weakening with the bursting of the late 1980s asset bubble.

news.title: Australia bank CEOs call for a fix to housing shortage
news.para: At a banking conference in Sydney, the heads of Commonwealth Bank, National Australia Bank and Westpac , Australia's top 3 lenders, blamed a housing supply shortage and urged local governments to speed up planning approvals.

news.title: New home sales in US fall by 0.3% in February 2024
news.para: "Housing activity is stabilizing as homebuilders appear to be building cheaper, and therefore, likely smaller homes," said Conrad DeQuadros, senior economic advisor at Brean Capital.

news.title: Luxury real estate has huge opportunity: Kaushal Kishore, Minister of State, Housing Ministry
news.para: Kaushal Kishore was speaking at an event organised by PHD Chamber of Commerce and Industry (PHDCCI) in New Delhi. He also highlighted the importance of the steps taken to provide housing for all and affordable housing.

news.title: Aeria raises US$1.8 million in pre-seed round led by Kalaari & Foundamental
news.para: Aeria will use the capital to expand its presence across Southeast Asia, Middle East and other Asian countries over the next year.

news.title: To finalise coastal plan, Goa begins comparing 2011 maps with survey plans
news.para: The discrepancies include village boundaries, survey plots, roads, khazan lands, and water bodies not being properly superimposed. The high tide line has also shifted towards land.

news.title: Kolkata civic body postpones demolition plan of five-storey building in Garden Reach
news.para: Kolkata Municipal Corporation faced resident resistance in Garden Reach, delaying a damaged building's demolition for alternative lodging and rehab details. The plan involved relocating families to Ramnagar community hall temporarily.

news.title: Pune: Keshavnagar residents battle severe water shortage amid little civic help
news.para: Chandresh Yadav, chairman of Anandtara Whitefield Residences in Keshavnagar, said, “My society of 280 flats is almost entirely dependent on water supplied by private tanker operators.

news.title: India has the opportunity to leapfrog bad practices and use cleaner solutions: Peter Templeton, CEO, USGBC
news.para: In an exclusive conversation, Peter Templeton, CEO, USGBC and P. Gopalakrishnan, managing director, GBCI (South East Asia & Middle East) talked about sustainability, construction industry’s role in reducing carbon emissions, carbon trading and much more.

news.title: Flex-space market size expected to touch 126 million sq ft by 2028: Report
news.para: Sectors like IT & ITeS, BFSI, consulting, e-commerce, manufacturing, and new-age startups, along with the continuous influx of global captive centers (GCCs) are driving demand.

news.title: 315Work Avenue aims to double its portfolio in next 18 months
news.para: Manas Mehrotra, founder of the company said: "We are also exploring opportunities to expand our reach by entering mall spaces and opening up shared offices to attract more clients."

news.title: DRA Homes to invest Rs 150 crore to develop commercial space in Chennai
news.para: DRA Homes plans to invest Rs 150 crore into the development of an A-grade office complex. It aims to lease the entire building of 1.1 lakh sq ft to a single client, with a rental rate of Rs. 110 per sq ft per month.

news.title: China pushes banks to speed approvals of new loans to developers: Sources
news.para: Most top domestic banks have so far shied away from significantly bolstering credit exposure to the crisis-hit sector despite repeated nudges from Beijing, dashing hopes of a revival in an industry crucial for the economy.

news.title: No hike in property tax in Bengaluru from April 1
news.para: State govt denies 2024-25 Bengaluru property tax revision. 2016 levy method remains. Police crackdown on fake news. Misinformation debunked. No property tax increase, reassuring residents.

news.title: Adam Neumann bids over $500 million to buy back WeWork: Source
news.para: Adam Neumann raised WeWork to be the most valuable U.S. startup, worth $47 billion, before his pursuit of expansion at the expense of profit and revelations about his eccentric behavior led to his ouster in 2019 and derailed what would have been a major initial public offering.

news.title: NCLT rejects promoter’s resolution plan in Wadhwa Buildcon insolvency matter
news.para: The matter, brought by the company’s financial creditor Bank of India, highlighted various irregularities in the approval process of the resolution plan, ultimately leading to its rejection.

news.title: Ethiopia to let foreigners own property: Prime Minister
news.para: Currently foreigners are barred from owning houses in Ethiopia, either residential or commercial buildings, which is seen as a hurdle to ongoing efforts to attract foreign investment to the Horn of Africa country.

news.title: China: Shimao Group lays out restructuring proposal
news.para: Under the proposal, Shimao intends to restructure all of its debt, amounting to around $11.7 billion in offshore notes, bonds and other credit facilities.

news.title: Sweden's SBB to buy back debt at 60% discount
news.para: The buyback will trim the struggling property company's debts, which amounted to some 62 billion Swedish crowns ($5.9 billion) at the end of last year.
